 Victoria]]\n* 2007: Honorary [[Doctor of Laws]], [[University of Prince Edward Island]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Prince Edward gives medals to P.E.I. soldiers|publisher=CTV|date=14 October 2007|url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20071014/prince_071014/20071014?hub=TopStories&s_name=|accessdate=11 July 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071130041857/http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20071014/prince_071014/20071014?hub=TopStories|archivedate=30 November 2007|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* 2013: Honorary [[Doctor of Laws]], [[University of Bath]]<ref name=\"Bath\"/>\n\n===Arms===\n{{Infobox COA wide\n|name           = the Earl of Wessex\n|image          = Coat of Arms of Edward, Earl of Wessex.svg\n|bannerimage    = Royal Standard of Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex.svg\n|badgeimage     =\n|notes          = The Earl's personal [[coat of arms]] is that of the [[Royal coat of arms of the United Kingdom]] with a label for difference\n|year_adopted   = 1983\n|coronet        = The [[coronet]] of a son of the sovereign Proper, thereon a lion statant gardant Or crowned of the same coronet charged with a label as in the arms.\n|crest          =\n|torse          =\n|helm           =\n|escutcheon     = Quarterly, 1st and 4th Gules three lions passant guardant in pale Or armed and langed Azure, 2nd Or a lion rampant Gules armed and langued Azure within a double tressure flory counterflory of the Second, 3rd Azure a harp Or stringed Argent\n|supporters     = Dexter, a lion rampant gardant Or imperially crowned Proper; Sinister, a unicorn Argent, armed, crined and unguled Or, gorged with a coronet Or composed of crosses patt\u00e9es and fleurs de lis a chain affixed thereto passing between the forelegs and reflexed over the back also Or\n|compartment    =\n|motto          = The Order of the Garter circlet.<br />'''[[Honi soit qui mal y pense]]'''<br />''(Shame be to him who thinks evil of it)''\n|orders         =\n|other_elements = The whole differenced by a label of three points Argent the central point charged with a [[Tudor rose]].\n|banner         = The [[Royal Standard of the United Kingdom]] labelled for difference as in his arms. (In Scotland: [[File:Royal Standard of Prince Edward, Earl of Forfar.svg|50px]])\n|badge          =\n|symbolism      = As with the Royal Arms of the United Kingdom. The first and fourth quarters are the arms of England, the second of Scotland, the third of Ireland.}}\n\n===Personal flag for Canada===\n{{Main|Royal standards of Canada#Other members of the Royal Family}}\n[[File:Royal Standard of Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex (in Canada).svg|thumb|Flag of the Earl of Wessex for use in Canada]]\n\nSince 2014, the Earl of Wessex has a personal [[heraldic flag]] for use in Canada. It is the [[Royal Arms of Canada]] in [[banner of arms|banner form]] defaced with a blue [[roundel (heraldry)|roundel]] surrounded by a wreath of gold maple leaves, within which is a depiction of an ''\"E\"'' surmounted by a coronet. Above the roundel is a white [[Label (heraldry)|label]] of three points, the centre one charged with a Tudor rose.<ref>{{cite web|title=Canadian Flags of the Royal Family|url=http://canadiancrown.gc.ca/eng/1396525887776|website=Canadian Crown|publisher=Government of Canada|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://reg.gg.ca/heraldry/pub-reg/project.asp?lang=e&ProjectID=2531 | title=The Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex | publisher=Office of the Governor General of Canada: Canadian Heraldic Authority | work=Public Register of Arms, Flags and Badges | accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center |ref=<ref>{{Cite book |last=Paget |first=Gerald|title=The Lineage and Ancestry of H.R.H. Prince Charles, Prince of Wales ''(2 vols)'' |location=Edinburgh |publisher=Charles Skilton |year=1977 |isbn=978-0-284-40016-1}}</ref>\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex'''\n|2= 2. [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip of Greece and Denmark]]\n|3= 3. [[Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]]\n|4= 4. [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]]\n|5= 5. [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]]\n|6= 6. [[George VI|George VI of the United Kingdom]]\n|7= 7. [[Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother|Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon]]\n|8= 8. [[George I of Greece]]\n|9= 9. [[Olga Constantinovna of Russia|Grand Duchess Olga Constantinovna of Russia]]\n|10= 10. [[Prince Louis of Battenberg]]\n|11= 11. [[Princess Victoria of Hesse and by Rhine]]\n|12= 12. [[George V|George V of the United Kingdom]]\n|13= 13. [[Mary of Teck|Princess Mary of Teck]]\n|14= 14. [[Claude Bowes-Lyon, 14th Earl of Strathmore and Kinghorne]]\n|15= 15. [[Cecilia Bowes-Lyon, Countess of Strathmore and Kinghorne|Cecilia Cavendish-Bentinck]]\n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of British princes]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=fn}}\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Spoken Wikipedia|En-Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex-article.ogg|12 July 2014}}\n{{Commons category|Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.royal.uk/the-earl-of-wessex |title=The Earl of Wessex|publisher=at the Royal Family website}}\n* {{Britannica|639997|Prince Edward, earl of Wessex}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0921844|name=Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Windsor]]|10 March|1964}}\n{{S-other|line}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Princess Eugenie, Mrs Jack Brooksbank]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Succession to the British throne]]|years=11th in line}}\n{{S-fol|after=[[James, Viscount Severn|Viscount Severn]]}}\n{{S-reg|uk}}\n{{S-new|rows=2|creation}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Earl of Wessex]]|years=1999\u2013present}}\n{{S-inc|rows=2|heir=[[James, Viscount Severn]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Earl of Forfar]]